üá∫üá∏The court granted a request by Missouri and Louisiana to remove the six Gates swindler Fauci and other officials in connection with conspiring with BigTech to suppress free speech.

On October 21, Missouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt announced that the United States District Court for the Western District of Louisiana had granted Missouri and Louisiana's request for testimony by senior federal government officials. 

https://ago.mo.gov/home/news/2022/10/21/court-orders-depositions-of-top-biden-officials-in-missouri-ag-s-case

The list for testimony includes Anthony Fauci, former White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki, White House Digital Strategy Director Rob Flaherty, Surgeon General Vivek Murty, CISA Director Jen Easterly and FBI Special Agent for Oversight Elvis Chan. 

The original lawsuit was filed by Missouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt and Louisiana Attorney General Jeff Landry on May 5, 2022. Missouri and Louisiana filed a motion for expedited pre-trial review on June 17, 2022, and that motion was granted on July 12, 2022, allowing Missouri and Louisiana to collect information and documents from Biden administration officials and social media companies.

"Upon discovering documentation of collusion between the Biden administration and social media companies to censor free speech, we immediately filed a motion to swear in these officials," Schmitt said, "It's time to shed light on this censorship exercise and get these officials to confess to the American People, and this ruling will allow us to do just that. We will continue to insist on the truth."

Full text of the resolution
